<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-077-187 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 161 863</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  August 26 1991 v25 n34 p33(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bechtel puts on Recital: RDBMS and 4GL tool smooth construction ofwaste facility. (Bechtel-Savannah River, Inc. uses Recital Corp.'sRecital relational database management system andfourth-generation language)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cusack, Sally.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Bechtel-Savannah River, Inc use Recital Corp's Recital relationaldata base management system (RDBMS) and fourth-generation language(4GL) to manage the data generated in a waste management projectfor the Department of Defense.andP;  Bechtel uses Recital to centralizeinformation.andP;  Approximately 25 various microcomputer-resident databases were used in the firm, so information required for differentgroups had to be moved physically between groups.andP;  Making theinformation centralized made it possible for everyone to accessdata at the same time on various DEC VAX machines.andP;  Bechtel uses aDEC/VAX terminal emulator and the microcomputer part of Recital toupload database files from microcomputers to the VAX.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bechtel Savannah River Inc. (Communication systems)Recital Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   Recital (Data base management system) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Data base management systemsRelational Data BasesFourth-Generation LanguagesProject Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>